Fresh-eyes review done on `src/blog/people/drafts/Keira-Knightley.md` — notes appended as a `FRESH EYES REVIEW (2026-06-12)` comment block at the bottom of the file. No body edits made.

The two biggest issues flagged:

1. **The Star Wars miss.** The cold open is built entirely on her signing Natalie Portman's autograph, and the draft never mentions she was cast at 12 as Portman's *decoy* (Sabé in The Phantom Menace) because they look alike — even their mothers mixed them up on set. The anecdote isn't random celebrity confusion; it's a 25-year echo of her literal first job being "looked at as somebody else." One sentence pays off the piece's own punchline.
2. **The filmography is thin for an actress profile.** Love Actually and The Imitation Game never appear — the draft says "Oscar nominations" plural but only ever names one. Related: it never asks *why* she's the corset queen, even though her on-record answer (she avoids modern roles because the female characters "nearly always get raped") is threat-assessment applied to script selection and supports the Type 6 thesis directly.

Also flagged: heavy anecdote duplication (the hypnotherapy red carpet appears four times across FAQ and body), the stress section repeating the Rabbit Hole's stress-to-3 paragraph, and a contrast-pair count closer to 4–5 than the ledger's claimed 2. The keep-list includes the Carney section (strongest in the piece), the BAFTA inner-thought beat, and the dollhouse bookend.

Sources: [ScreenRant — Knightley's Star Wars casting via Portman resemblance](https://screenrant.com/natalie-portman-and-keira-knightley-not-releated-star-wars-casting-resemblance/), [May 4 Be With You — even their mothers mixed them up on set](https://may4bewithyou.com/even-natalie-portman-and-keira-knightleys-own-mothers-mixed-them-up-on-set-when-they-were-both-in-full-amidala-makeup-ty95/), [Cinemablend — Portman on being mistaken for Knightley](https://www.cinemablend.com/movies/natalie-portman-mistaken-another-actress-all-the-time-keira-knightley)
